# cc02379138e24e4e9e8d0cc73356f4f0
#: ../../admin-guide/files/ip_allow.config.en.rst:40
msgid ""
"where src_ip is the IP address or range of IP addresses of the client(s)."
" The action ``ip_allow`` enables the specified client(s) to access the "
"Traffic Server proxy cache, and ``ip_deny`` denies the specified "
"client(s) to access the Traffic Server proxy cache. Multiple method "
"keywords can be specified (method=GET method=HEAD), or multiple methods "
"can be separated by an '\\|' (method=GET\\|HEAD). The method keyword is "
"optional and it is defaulted to ALL. This supports ANY string as the HTTP"
" method, meaning no validation is done to check wether it is a valid HTTP"
" method. This allows you to create filters for any method that your "
"origin may require, this is especially useful if you use newer methods "
"that aren't know to trafficserver (such as PROPFIND) or if your origin "
"uses an http-ish protocol."
msgstr ""

